Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: Clerk Joyce did not enter the CBS entry on 10/19/22.  Clerk Joyce entered a SIBSI entry and a CBAM entry on 10/19/22.

2:13 PM Defendant Rocco Antonio White in court.  Attorney Allison Cogbill in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Address is 6820 Tower avenue, Apt. 5, Superior. Court recites charges against defendant and possible penalties. Defendant advised of right to consult an attorney. Defendant pleads not guilty. Court accepts plea. 
State notes no FTAs, Asks for 500 signature bond, no contact with KM, except 3rd party for parenting time.
Defendant has no objection.
Court orders $500 signature bond, with conditions of no contact with KM, except for 3rd party for parenting time. Court is informed defendant was served with restraining order yesterday with terms of no contact with KM. Court orders absolutely no contact with KM.
Defendant informed of right to attorney form in DA's office.
Status conference scheduled for November 21, 2022 at 11:00 am.

Court recalls case at 2:36 PM. Defendant in Court. Allison Cogbill in Court. Defendant indicates already posted $500 previously. Court indicates will retain that $500. Court amends bond to $500 cash, conditions to continue. Signature bond vacated.
